- Wed 25 Sep 2019. Update
[CMRE (Comite Multisectoriel de la Riposte a la maladie a virus Ebola), machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://mailchi.mp/3dcebce216f1/situation-pidmiologique-au-24-septembre-2019?e=9281954762
and https://crofsblogs.typepad.com/h5n1/2019/09/drc-ebola-cmre-update-september-24.html

Epidemiological situation in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri on 23 Sep 2019:
Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 3170, of which 3059 are confirmed and 111 are probable. In total, there were 2119 deaths (2007 confirmed and 111 probable) and 975 people healed.
- 447 suspected cases under investigation; 1 probable case was validated in Ituri at Mambasa;
- 2 new confirmed cases in North Kivu at Oicha;
- 1 new confirmed death in Ituri in Mandima;
- 4 persons recovered and left the ETC including 3 in North Kivu, notably 2 in Beni and 1 in Katwa, as well as 1 in Ituri at Komanda;
- No health worker is among the new confirmed cases. The cumulative number of confirmed/probable cases among health workers is 160 (5% of all confirmed/probable cases), including 41 deaths.

News
-----
- A new probable case has been validated in the health zone of Mambasa in Ituri. This is a 39-year-old woman, a traditional healer, who died in the Salama health area in the Madidi district. She was not listed as a contact and was not vaccinated;
- The start date of the signs goes back to 1 Sep 2019, with the period of time of exposure of 15-28 Aug 2019, by fever, headache, anorexia, and chest pain;
- From 1-3 Sep 2019, this woman self-medicated at home and was hospitalized from 4-6 Sep 2019 in St. Peter Medical Center. The alert was launched on 4 Sep 2019 following the alteration of the conscience, the reason for consultation at St. Peter's. It was investigated and validated, but the family categorically refused the transfer to the ETC. Persuasion was unsuccessful;
- The patient was brought home by her family on 6 Sep 2019, where she died at around 10 p.m. Oral sampling and dignified and secure burial did not occur by refusal of this family;
-This woman was a known contact of one of the patients who died on 18 Aug 2019 and confirmed on 19 Aug 2019 that she had been treated on 16 Aug 2019. She had refused the listing;
- 45 contacts are listed around this traditional healer, 3 of whom became suspicious and confirmed positive for Ebola virus disease. These are her husband, mother, and son, all admitted to ETC Komanda;
- This probable case was notified on 4 Sep 2019.

Vaccination
------------
- The expanded program of vaccines has received 4320 doses of vaccine at the national level;
- Since vaccination began on [8 Aug 2018], 227 230 people have been vaccinated;
- The only vaccine to be used in this outbreak is the rVSV-ZEBOV vaccine, manufactured by the pharmaceutical group Merck, following approval by the Ethics Committee in its decision of 20 May 2018.

Monitoring entry points
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the total number of travelers checked (temperature rise) at the sanitary control points is 98 080 726;
- To date, a total of 111 entry points (PoE) and sanitary control points (PoCs) have been set up in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri to protect the country's major cities and prevent the spread of the epidemic in neighboring countries.

