- Fri 27 Sep 2019
[The Japan Times, abridged, edited]
https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2019/09/27/national/japan-imports-ebola-virus/#.XY4UKhZlCaM

Japan imports Ebola virus for research ahead of 2020 Olympics visitor influx

Strains of Ebola and 4 other deadly viruses have been imported to Japan for the development of diagnostic kits ahead of an expected influx of visitors for the 2020 Olympics and Paralympics in Tokyo, a governmental research institute said Friday [27 Sep 2019].

The viruses were taken to a branch facility of the National Institute of Infectious Diseases in western Tokyo's Musashimurayama on Wednesday and Thursday. [25 and 26 Sep 2019], according to an institute official.

The government obtained Ebola, Lassa, South American ? Crimean-Congo, and Marburg viruses from 2 foreign research facilities.

The 5 viruses did not previously exist in Japan.

